A young girl suffered serious injuries when she was hit by a motorbike.The child, who is about 10 years old, was on foot when she was hurt in the crash on Coleshill Road in Atherstone, Warwickshire, shortly after 17:00 BST on Tuesday, police said.She was treated at the scene before being taken to Birmingham Children's Hospital, West Midlands Ambulance Service said."She was assessed and had sustained potentially life-threatening injuries," a spokesperson said.
Warwickshire Police said the youngster remained in hospital on Wednesday and their investigations were ongoing.
